Package insa.h4401.model

Provides the classes necessary to create the model for this application.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Arc
    This class represents a road, that goes from a node to another one.
    Delivery
    This class represents a delivery point, comparable by delivery times.
    Map
    This class represents a map, a graph, composed of arcs (streets) and nodes (crossroads).
    Node
    This class represents a node, which can be the beginning point of at least one outgoing street.
    Path
    This class represents an ordered collection of arcs to follow to reach a delivery or a warehouse.
    PathGraph
    This class represents a graph with vertices representing Path object, allowing to find the best way to visit each node thanks to a ITSP algorithm for example.
    Planning
    This class represents a planning, a collection of deliveries contained in timeslots.
    Route
    This class represents a route, with the entire paths to follow to execute every delivery.
    TimeSlot
    This class represents a time slot, with a start time and an end time.

Package insa.h4401.model Description

Provides the classes necessary to create the model for this application.

The model is managed by a controller ModelManager (see package controller)
